history.text: Wow, I'm surprised at the Rotten Tomatoes score of 5.8, I really like that.
I know! I love Leonardo DiCaprio, he was great as a billionaire.
I love the scenes with his wild parties at his house. They were great.
I really like the plot of this movie, Leo and Tobey were good in this.
Yes, with the stars they had in the movie, you can see what it had a $190 million budget!
Great CinemaScore as well! It's nice to know it was also written and directed by Leonardo DiCaprio while starring on the movie itself!
I really didn't like the character that Joel Edgerton plays as Tom Buchanan. He was so mean just because Gatsby had new money.
Yes, that's why I hope Jay Gatsby made Daisy Buchanan who's in a relationship with Joel Edgerton show up in Jay's wild parties.
The Roaring Twenties seemed like a wild time.
What I like about the Great Gatsby is that it lived up to its genre, it's so romantic!
It really is, Nick Carraway narration  and I'm so glad his doctor had him write his stories of Jay Gatsby down so we have  the movie.

Good point, his thoughts were written down with passion leading to a great movie. But sadly, he 
abandoned writing!
Yes, he did abandon writing when he moved from the midwest.
I wonder Nick Carraway felt when his house was next to Gatsby who often held wild parties at home.
I wonder how Nick Carraway felt*
Nick I think realized Gatsby was hopeful about Daisy when he came back home and say Gatsby reaching toward the green light at the Buchanan dock.
Wow, Gatsby admited he was penniless when he was born and James Gatz was his real name .
Yes, that was an amazing scene when they were talking about Myrtle's death when she thought Gatsby's car was Tom's.
I know, it was interesting when Nick decided not to tell Gatsby when he overheard Daisy accepted a promise from Tome of having to take care of every thing.
Yes. Oh my gosh, remember when Gatsby tells Tom he was with Daisy? That was intense!
Gatsby being a billionaire, having an affair is surely interesting! That's why Tom accused Gatsby.
I know, Tom really accused Gatsby of making his money from bootlegging with mobsters! How rude.
My gosh, Gatsby was shot by of George!
Isn't that horrible? And so sad that Nick is the only one that attended his funeral besides reporters.
Daisy even left with Tom to New York! What a sad love story.
No wonder Nick leaves after taking a final walk through Gatsby's deserted mansion.
It's unfortunate that Gatsby is named by the media as the lover and killer of Myrtle.
Yes, it's so sad that Nick ended up typing his memoir in the sanitorium.
I know! Great movie!
Nick created a great title for his memories with Gatsby.

uid1response.feedback: Great conversation! I enjoyed reading and imagining the movie from the document.

uid2response.feedback: Other person was VERY slow to respond, making this take over 40 minutes! You should lower the time between responses that we can abort.
